messages.message: Is anyone currently responsible for github integration/CICD or is it frozen on the current state?
Do you mean the SDLC stuff?

If so, that work is falling into the core-services domain and it’s not frozen. @Aaron Vontell put together a beta version of it, but a bunch of work still needs to go into productionizing it. I think Kerry mentioned she might want to take it as an internship project for now?
Yeah, i was following the guide to hook it up to my github account and it was beyond difficult, minor tweaks could make it much easier.
If it’s more involved/Aaron doesn’t have bandwidth, feel free to kick it over and we’ll take a look
You know me, I will always make sure to kick things around :wink:

@Matt - I’m hoping to have an intern to work on it for the second half of the summer. We are doing some Marketplace work for the first half. If you can write down your feedback somewhere (like in a Jira ticket or in a google doc) and share with me, that’d be really helpful. We’ll try to to get to it, if not this summer, in Q3.
